article.headline: Oral Roberts 74, UMKC 56
article.story: KANSAS CITY, Mo. (AP) -- Caleb Green had 15 points Monday night to lead Oral Roberts to a 74-56 Mid-Continent Conference victory over Missouri-Kansas City at Kemper Arena. The Golden Eagles (12-9, 7-2) snapped a four-game winning streak by the Kangaroos (9-11, 6-4) in the series between the two schools. Green, who did not have a point in the first 19 minutes of the game, had 13 second-half points in leading three Golden Eagles in double figures. Chris Riouse came off the bench to score 13 and Mickey Michalec added 11 points and 11 rebounds. UMKC never led in the game, and trailed 28-19 at the half. Oral Roberts increased the margin to 15 on a rebound basket by Green that made it 44-29 with 11:25 left. The Eagles' biggest lead was 74-52 after a free throw by Moses Ehmabe with 55 seconds left. Quinton Day led the Kangaroos with 26 points, but he was just 8-of-26 from the field and 3-of-12 from behind the 3-point line. UMKC shot just 20-of-68 from the field for 29 percent, while the Eagles hit 47 percent (27-of-57). Oral Roberts also outrebounded UMKC 50-29, led by Larry Owens with 13.
